								<h1>Alireza Sadeghi</h1>
								<span class="profession">Ph.D. Candidate</span>
								<div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

								<h2>About</h2>
								<p>
									I am a software engineering Ph.D. Candidate at <a href="http://www.informatics.uci.edu" target="_blank">Informatics Departments</a> of <a
										href="http://www.ics.uci.edu" target="_blank">Donald Bren School of Information & Computer Sciences</a>, University of California, Irvine.
									As a member of <a href="https://seal.ics.uci.edu" target="_blank">SEAL</a> Lab, I'm working under supervision of <a
										href="http://malek.ics.uci.edu" target="_blank">Dr.Sam Malek</a>. <br> I received the B.Sc. degree in computer (software) engineering
									and M.Sc. degree in information technology from <a href="http://ce.sharif.edu/" target="_blank">Sharif University of Technology</a> in 2008
									and 2010.
								</p>
								<p>My research interests focus on software engineering, specifically, applying program analysis techniques in the domain of mobile
									applications, particularly for the security assessment.</p>
								<br />

